%T A393890 2095784572672,111307423700480,6394395028321024,395076311257767936,
%U A393890 26126329030730590208,1841588202580128978944,137861931861876529504512,10925164047935651951794176,913857369192040571560988672,80472788792386167072299008000
%N A393890 G.f. A(x) satisfies 5*A(x) = 1 + x + 4*A(x*A(x)).
%H A393890 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A393890/b393890.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..300</a>
%F A393890 G.f. A(x) = Sum_{n>=0} a(n)*x^n satisfies the following formulas.
%F A393890 (1) 5*A(x) = 1 + x + 4*A(x*A(x)).
%F A393890 (2) A(x) = 1 + Sum_{n>=0} 4^n * B^n(x) / 5^(n+1), where B(x) = x*A(x) and B^n(x) denotes the n-th iteration of B(x) with B^0(x) = x.
%F A393890 (3) 4*A(x) = 5*F(x) - x/F(x) - 1, where F(x) = A(x/F(x)) = x/Series_Reversion(x*A(x)).
%F A393890 a(n) ~ c * n^(n + 3/10 + 3*log(5/4)) / (exp(n) * log(5/4)^n), where c = 0.197680083007236432113... - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 06 2026
%F A393890 From _Seiichi Manyama_, Apr 06 2026: (Start)
%F A393890 Let b(n,k) = [x^n] A(x)^k.
%F A393890 b(0,1) = b(1,1) = 1;   b(n,1) =     4 * Sum_{j=1..n-1} b(j,1) * b(n-j,j).
%F A393890 For k > 1, b(0,k) = 1; b(n,k) = (1/n) * Sum_{j=1..n} ((k+1)*j-n) * b(j,1) * b(n-j,k).
%F A393890 a(n) = b(n,1). (End)
%e A393890 G.f.: A(x) = 1 + x + 4*x^2 + 48*x^3 + 912*x^4 + 22784*x^5 + 690496*x^6 + 24314624*x^7 + 969209152*x^8 + 42986764544*x^9 + ...
%e A393890 RELATED SERIES.
%e A393890 A(x*A(x)) = 1 + x + 5*x^2 + 60*x^3 + 1140*x^4 + 28480*x^5 + 863120*x^6 + 30393280*x^7 + 1211511440*x^8 + 53733455680*x^9 + ...
%e A393890 where A(x) = (1 + x)/5 + (4/5)*A(x*A(x)).
%e A393890 If F(x) = A(x/F(x)), then
%e A393890 F(x) = 1 + x + 3*x^2 + 38*x^3 + 723*x^4 + 18098*x^5 + 549086*x^6 + 19349740*x^7 + 771736003*x^8 + 34243429882*x^9 + ...
%e A393890 where 4*A(x) = 5*F(x) - x/F(x) - 1.
%e A393890 RELATED TABLE.
%e A393890 The table of coefficients in the n-th iteration of x*A(x) begins
%e A393890   n = 0: [1, 0,  0,   0,     0,      0,        0, ...];
%e A393890   n = 1: [1, 1,  4,  48,   912,  22784,   690496, ...];
